About Winter Haven
About Winter Haven
The Winter Haven area, between Tampa and Orlando, is home to beautiful lakes, a majestic tower, a world-class collection of vintage aircrafts and the largest LEGOLAND in the world. So, there are plenty of places to play, explore and reflect. Visitors will find a variety of hotels, motels and bed and breakfasts close to all the things you’ll enjoy. And whether you are looking for a quick bite, your favorite fast food or gourmet fare, the Winter Haven area is home to a number of delightful restaurants.
Here are some fun things to do in Winter Haven and its surrounding area.
Visit
LEGOLAND
Florida, the largest LEGOLAND in the world and located in Winter Haven.
Hunt for treasures from another time in the Winter Haven part of
Florida’s Antique Loop
.
Let your imagination soar at
The Fantasy of Flight
, a working restoration facility that has the world’s largest collection of vintage aircraft, among other unique heritage highlights in the Lakeland-Winter Haven area.
Discover the largest single-site collection of
Frank Lloyd Wright Designs at Florida Southern College
, a National Historic Landmark comprised of distinctly American structures. The nearby Lakeland campus is known as Wright’s “Child in the Sun.”
Revel in the elegance and grandeur of a show at the
Polk Theatre
, nearby in Lakeland. It’s a 1928 vaudeville movie palace that has a full calendar of films, speakers, musicals and guided tours.
Surround yourself with lush landscapes and the soothing sound of carillon bells at
Bok Tower Gardens
in nearby Lake Wales. The property – sitting near Iron Mountain at one of the highest points in Florida – offers sweeping views of a valley of towns and orange groves below.
Grab a napkin and plan your trip for January so you can pig out at the
Lakeland Pigfest
, where more than 150 barbecue teams fire up main dishes, sides, sauces and desserts.
Take a short drive to Plant City, home of the
Florida Strawberry Festival
every March and the year-round fun of Dinosaur World, with its 80-foot dinosaur models and authentic fossils.
Dare to experience what it feels like jumping from an airplane at 13,500 feet at
Skydive City
in nearby Zephyrhills.
Discover small-town art treasures at
Lake Wales Art Center
, the
Lake Wales Museum & Cultural Center
, and the
Polk Museum of Art
.
Repost from
VisitFlorida.com

About Us
WE ARE UNDER NEW OWNERSHIP
OUR NEW NAME IS
SOUTHERN DUCKS RV RESORT
We are delighted you stopped by to inquire about our little oasis.  Centrally located in beautiful Winter Haven, FL, our park offers a community that takes pride in itself, its guests and residents.  If you are looking for a clean and comfortable atmosphere, we’d love to have you for a night, a week, a month, a season or permanently!
